3Sum Short Notes

Goal:
Find all unique triplets whose sum is 0.

Core Idea

Sort the array

Fix one number

Use two pointers to find the other two

Skip duplicates

Why Sort?

Enables two-pointer logic

Makes duplicate removal easy

Steps

Sort nums

Loop index i

Skip duplicate nums[i]

Set pointers

l = i + 1, r = end

While l < r:

If sum < 0 → l += 1

If sum > 0 → r -= 1

If sum == 0:

Store triplet

Skip duplicates

Move both pointers

Code
from typing import List

class Solution:
    def threeSum(self, nums: List[int]) -> List[List[int]]:
        nums.sort()
        res = []

        for i in range(len(nums) - 2):
            if i and nums[i] == nums[i - 1]:
                continue

            l, r = i + 1, len(nums) - 1
            while l < r:
                s = nums[i] + nums[l] + nums[r]
                if s < 0: l += 1
                elif s > 0: r -= 1
                else:
                    res.append([nums[i], nums[l], nums[r]])
                    l += 1; r -= 1
                    while l < r and nums[l] == nums[l - 1]: l += 1
                    while l < r and nums[r] == nums[r + 1]: r -= 1
        return res

Complexity

Time: O(n²)

Space: O(1) (excluding output)

Interview Signal

If you understand why pointers move, this problem is DONE.
If not, you’re just memorizing code.

Next logical step: 4Sum → Same pattern, more control.
